oring and cotensoring a Poincar\\'e $\\infty$-category over a\nfinite simplicial complex, a construction featuring prominently in the\ndefinition of the L- and Grothendieck-Witt spectra that we consider in the next\ninstalment.\n  Finally, we define already here the 0-th Grothendieck-Witt group of a\nPoincar\\'e $\\infty$-category using generators and relations. We extract its\nbasic properties, relating it in particular to the 0-th L- and algebraic\nK-groups, a relation upgraded in the second instalment to a fibre sequence of\nspectra which plays a key role in our applications.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 15 Sep 2020 17:03:43 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 26 Mar 2021 20:43:28 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 27 Dec 2021 15:46:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-28"}
