 salts negative\neffective surface potentials in the range from $-10$ mV for NaCl down to about\n$-80$ mV for NaNip, consistent with typical experimental ranges for the\nzeta-potential. We discuss how these values depend on the surface definition\nand compare them to the explicitly calculated electrostatic potentials near the\nNP surface, which are highly oscillatory in the $\\pm 0.5$ V range.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 15 Sep 2020 17:30:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-04-14"}
