e the post-reionization ionizing background fluctuations\naccurately with ray-tracing codes. Lastly, we argue that the strong dependence\nof the post-reionization ionizing background on the value of the reduced speed\nof light found in many simulations signals that the ionizing photon mean free\npath is several times larger in such simulations than the observationally\nmeasured value.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 15 Sep 2020 18:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 6 Dec 2020 19:26:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-03-03"}
